address: 107 Yeonghwasa-ro, Gueui-dong, Gwangjin-gu, Seoul, South Korea
description: Mount Echa Yonghua Temple is an old temple with a history of nearly 100 years. It is located at the foot of Mount Echa. The environment here is quiet and there are colorful lanterns hanging in the courtyard. There are three golden Buddhas in the Daxiong Hall. Tourists often come to watch.

address: Veloso Hongdae  46 Jandari-ro, Mapo-gu, Seoul (Basement of Studio Building 372-6, Seogyo-dong)

place_name: The Children’s Museum of the National Folk Museum of Korea
description: The Children's Museum, located in Seoul, South Korea, has a wide variety of exhibits in the museum, involving paintings, animals, scientific exploration, human body exploration, social culture and other fields. There is also a drama school. The museum also regularly holds colorful cultural activities.
